    // 9. KINUNOT FROM DONSOL
    [
        'source_url' => 'https://www.lakwatseralovers.com/kinunot-donsol-sorsogon',
        'source_blog_name' => 'Lakwatsera Lovers',
        'source_image_url' => null,
        'title' => 'Kinunot in Donsol: A Bicol Fish Dish on the Sorsogon Coast',
        'slug' => 'kinunot-donsol-sorsogon-fish-dish',
        'excerpt' => 'Kinunot is a Bicolano stingray dish in coconut cream and malunggay. Donsol in Sorsogon is the home version. Here is a calm food trip note.',
        'content_html' => <<<'HTML'
<p>Kinunot is a Bicolano dish of flaked stingray or shark meat braised in coconut cream with malunggay and chili. The fish is shredded by hand (kinunot means "tugged" or "pinched") and the dish leans creamy, peppery, and slightly briny. Donsol in Sorsogon is one of the home villages for the dish, served alongside the famous whale shark interaction tourism that puts the town on the map.</p>
<p>This is a calm food note paired with a whale shark trip if you are timing the season right. Tara, here is the kwento.</p>
<h2>Donsol Town</h2>
<p>Donsol is a small coastal town in Sorsogon, around an hour from Legazpi by van. The town built its tourism on butanding (whale shark) interaction from December to May, peaking in February to April. Outside the whale shark season the town is quiet, the carinderias still cook the Bicol-Sorsogon plates, and the food is the reason to come if you are not chasing the fish.</p>
<h2>Where to Eat Kinunot in Donsol</h2>
<p>The carinderias along the Donsol town center and around the Visitor Center serve kinunot when the fish is available. The dish is not on every menu every day; supply depends on what the fishermen brought in. Ask the kitchen if they have it before sitting down. The standard pairing is steamed rice and a side of laing.</p>
<h2>Vitton Beach Resort and the Carinderias Nearby</h2>
<p>The carinderia row along Vitton in Donsol serves kinunot, ginataang isda, and adobong pusit. The setting is by the beach, the breeze is real, and the kitchen is closer to home cooking than restaurant cooking. Pair with sili leaves saluyot for a green side.</p>
<h2>The Stingray Question</h2>
<p>Traditional kinunot uses pating (shark) or pagi (stingray). Both fish are subject to conservation conversations and sustainability concerns; in recent years some Donsol carinderias have shifted to other fleshy fish like tuna or marlin while keeping the kinunot name and method. Ask the kitchen what they used. If you are particular about shark-free eating, request tuna kinunot or marlin kinunot.</p>
<h2>The Whale Shark Connection</h2>
<p>Donsol's whale shark tourism is the season-defining draw. Boats leave from the Donsol Visitor Center in the early morning. Snorkel-only interaction, no touching, strict rules. The kinunot lunch after a successful interaction is the natural pair. If you came specifically for the whale sharks, treat the kinunot as the calm food memory of the trip.</p>
<h2>Other Bicol-Sorsogon Plates to Try</h2>
<p>Pair the kinunot with a few Sorsogon-side specialties: tinapayan (fermented anchovy spread), ginataang santol (santol fruit in coconut cream), and pinangat na isda. The Bicol-Sorsogon plate spread is wider than Bicol Express and laing alone.</p>
<h2>Getting There</h2>
<p>Fly to Legazpi from Manila in one hour. From Legazpi airport, a van or bus to Donsol takes around one hour. By bus from Manila, the trip is 12 hours overnight to Sorsogon City then a jeepney to Donsol.</p>
<h2>When to Go</h2>
<p>December to May for whale shark season. February to April is the peak. The food is available year-round but the energy of the town is highest during whale shark months. Avoid the August to November typhoon stretch.</p>
<h2>Stay Notes</h2>
<p>Donsol has small inns, homestays, and a few beachfront places along Vitton. Stay one or two nights. Sorsogon City is 30 minutes east if you want a bigger town for the night.</p>
<p>Kinunot is a coastal Bicol dish you only really get to taste in Sorsogon. Donsol is the quiet home village, and a calm afternoon kinunot lunch is the easy paired memory with a whale shark morning.</p>
